# AIMn Project Synchronization Guide
## Complete Guide to Keep PC, PythonAnywhere, and Git in Sync

---

## OVERVIEW
This guide helps you synchronize three locations:
1. **Your PC** (local development)
2. **PythonAnywhere** (live server)
3. **Git Repository** (version control)

---

## PART 1: CURRENT SITUATION CHECK

### Before Starting, Identify What You Have:
- Your PC: Has older version
- Git: Needs to be updated

---

## PART 2: THREE-WAY SYNC PROCESS

### STEP 1: Update Your PC (Local Computer)

**Option A: If you have the file downloaded from Claude**
```
1. Locate the downloaded file: aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html
2. Navigate to your local project folder on PC
  Example: C:\Users\YourName\Projects\AIMn\templates\
3. Replace the old file with the new one
4. Rename if needed to match your project structure
```

**Option B: If you want to create fresh on PC**
```
1. Open your text editor (VS Code, Notepad++, etc.)
2. Copy the content from the downloaded file
3. Save to your project location:
  YourProject\templates\aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html
```

---

### STEP 2: Upload to PythonAnywhere

**Method 1: Using PythonAnywhere Web Interface (EASIEST)**
```
1. Go to: https://www.pythonanywhere.com
2. Login to your account
3. Click "Files" tab at the top
4. Navigate to your templates folder:
  /home/MeirNiv/mysite/templates/
  (or wherever your templates are stored)
5. Click "Upload a file"
6. Select: aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html
7. If file exists, it will ask to overwrite - click YES
8. Click the green "Reload" button on your Web tab
```

**Method 2: Using PythonAnywhere Bash Console (ADVANCED)**
```bash
# Open a Bash console on PythonAnywhere
cd ~/mysite/templates/

# If you have the file locally, you can use SFTP to upload
# Or edit directly in PythonAnywhere
nano aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html
# Paste content, Ctrl+X, Y, Enter to save
```

---

### STEP 3: Commit to Git

**3A: If Git is Already Setup**
```bash
# Open terminal/command prompt on your PC
cd C:\Users\YourName\Projects\AIMn

# Check status
git status

# Add the changed file
git add templates/aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html

# Commit with descriptive message
git commit -m "Update scanner: Add trading hours detection (yellow for closed markets), FUTURES symbols (GC-GOLD, ES-SPX, CL-OIL), fix color indicators"

# Push to remote repository
git push origin main
# (or "git push origin master" depending on your branch name)
```

**3B: If Git is NOT Setup Yet**
```bash
# First time setup - Do this once
cd C:\Users\YourName\Projects\AIMn

# Initialize git repository
git init

# Add remote repository (replace with your actual Git URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YourUsername/AIMn.git

# Add all files
git add .

# First commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: AIMn Auto-Trading Scanner"

# Push to remote
git push -u origin main
```

---

## PART 3: PULL FROM GIT TO PYTHONANYWHERE

**After pushing to Git, update PythonAnywhere from Git:**

```bash
# On PythonAnywhere Bash Console
cd ~/mysite

# If git is already cloned
git pull origin main

# If first time - clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/AIMn.git

# Reload your web app
# Go to Web tab and click green "Reload" button
```

---

## PART 4: DAILY WORKFLOW (RECOMMENDED)

### When You Make Changes:

**Scenario A: Changes on PC Update PC & Git**
