## PART 5: COMMON ISSUES & SOLUTIONS

### Issue 1: "Git not found" on PythonAnywhere
```bash
# Git is pre-installed on PythonAnywhere
# If issues, verify:
which git
# Should show: /usr/bin/git
```

### Issue 2: "Permission denied" when pushing to Git
```bash
# Setup SSH key or use HTTPS with credentials
# For HTTPS, Git will prompt for username/password
# Or setup Personal Access Token (recommended)
```

### Issue 3: "Merge conflict" when pulling
```bash
# If you edited same file in two places:
git pull origin main
# Git will show conflict
# Edit the file, remove conflict markers
# Then:
git add .
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflict"
git push origin main
```

### Issue 4: PythonAnywhere shows old version after upload
```bash
# Always reload your web app!
# Go to Web tab )

# 2. Copy to your PC project folder
# Example: C:\Users\Meir\Projects\AIMn\templates\

# 3. Commit to Git (on PC)
cd C:\Users\Meir\Projects\AIMn
git add templates/aimn_flowing_scanner_auto.html
git commit -m "Update scanner: trading hours, futures symbols, color fixes"
git push origin main

# 4. Update PythonAnywhere
# Option A: Upload via Files tab (easiest)
# Option B: Pull from Git (best practice)
#   - Go to Bash console on PythonAnywhere
cd ~/mysite
git pull origin main
#   - Click Reload button on Web tab
```

